Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into wedges about the size of
your index finger (no need to peel!). Spread in a single layer on a #baking tray{}
(use two #baking trays{} if you can't spread out the wedges in a single layer - you
don't want to crowd them!). Sprinkle over half the @garlic salt{1/2%portion} and cook
on the top shelf of your oven until browned on the outside, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Split each @brioche bun{2} in half and grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. In a
#bowl{} combine the @British beef mince{240%g}, remaining @garlic salt{1/2%portion},
@dried oregano{1}, @panko breadcrumbs{20%g}, half the @tomato ketchup{1/2} and a few
grinds of @black pepper{}. Divide the beef mixture into equal portions, one per person,
then, with your hands, form into burger patties roughly 1 1/2cm thick.

> TIP: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Heat a splash of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, gently add in
the burger patties and cook for ~{5-7%minutes} on each side, or until the meat is fully
cooked with no pink bits remaining. When ready, pop the cheese on top of the burgers,
turn the heat to low and add a splash of water to the pan. Cover with a #lid{} or
some #foil{} and leave for ~{2-3%minutes} so the cheese melts.

While the burgers cook, cut one slice of @medium tomato{1}(sliced) per person and chop
the rest of the @medium tomato{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks). Put the chunks into a bowl
with three quarters of the @wild rocket{40%g}.

When the burgers are cooked, remove them from the pan and allow to rest on a
#board{} for a couple of minutes. Wipe out the pan with some #kitchen paper{} and pop
back on medium-high heat. Toast the buns in your pan for ~{1-2%minutes} on each side.

Drizzle a little oil over the rocket and tomato salad and add a pinch of salt and
pepper. Spread a little of the remaining @tomato ketchup{1/2} on each toasted bun.
Place a burger on top, then add a tomato slice and some remaining rocket. Serve with
the sweet potato wedges and salad on the side. Enjoy!